                    <h1>Developer Accessibility Component Guide</h1>
                    <p>Welcome to the guide designed to help developers create accessible web applications. This resource provides components, code snippets, and best practices for building inclusive experiences.</p>
                </section>

                <section id="components">
                    <h2>Components Library</h2>

                    <article>
                        <h3>Alert Component</h3>
                        <pre>
&lt;div role="alert" aria-live="assertive"&gt;
    &lt;p&gt;Your changes have been saved successfully.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
                        </pre>
                        <p>Description: Alerts are used to convey important information. Ensure they are announced by assistive technologies by using appropriate ARIA roles.</p>
                    </article>

                    <article>
                        <h3>Button Component</h3>
                        <pre>
&lt;button type="button" aria-label="Submit Form"&gt;
    &lt;span class="visually-hidden"&gt;Submit&lt;/span&gt;
    &lt;svg aria-hidden="true" focusable="false" width="24" height="24"&gt;
        &lt;use href="#icon-submit"&gt;&lt;/use&gt;
    &lt;/svg&gt;
&lt;/button&gt;
                        </pre>
                        <p>Description: Button element accessible to all users, including those using screen readers.</p>
                    </article>

                    <!-- Add more components as needed -->
                </section>

